gomodel:SYNGO_1252  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099059 replaced by GO:0048787" , "Rationale: Here we report on the subcellular localization of these receptors in the SCN, as revealed by an exten- sively characterized antibody to the\n\n12/9/2017 Pim\n- Literal: \"GABAA-receptor immunoreactivity is associated with the terminal plasma membrane and also occupies the intercellular cleft adjacent to a GABA-negative terminal (T2) D, dendrite. (b) Three GABAergic terminals (T1, T2, T3), two of which (T1, T3) express GABAA-receptor immunoreactivity associated with the terminal plasma membrane.\". Experimental description: Fourteen adult rats of the Sprague-Dawley strain were used for light and electron microscopic immunocytochemical analysis of GABAA receptors in the SCN." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
